A certain amazon had made sure the Queen was full aware that a Roman was not only in Amazon Lands, but in Labry's. The heart of Themiscrya. Unknown men were NOT allowed in Themiscrya, and being a Roman, it was much, much worse.<br>
<br>
Queen De'Lerium pushed open the door with a bang and gazed around the tavern with cold sea green eyes.<br>
Spotting the male, she walked over briskly, unsheathing her sword. She walked up behind him, grabbing ahandfull of his hair, and pulling back his head, her sword went to his throat, and she held it there firmly, one false move and his throat would be sliced open like so much meat.<br>
<br>
She looked to Cyrene<br>
&quot;What is the meaning of this, serving a Roman in our lands. Mayhaps you should know more about the Amazons past before you go welcoming every stranger who sets foot here in the City of the Amazons.&quot;<br>
<br>
Her eyes flashed anger, rage. She hated the Romans as much as the Centuars for what they did to her people. <p>         ~~* De'Lerium *~~ &lt;br&gt;<br>
