<br>
&quot;Forgive me my Queen, for I saw not a Roman, not a man, but a starving human being.&quot;  Controlling her own temper, she stepped back away from the table and around the side. &quot;Call me a foolish old woman, for I was a mother to sons once.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I was under the impression it was my job to make strangers welcome. Then again I am old and set in my ways.&quot; Taking a deep breath she met the Queen's eyes unwavering, &quot;I left what you would call normal civilization because of prejudices.  You are right, I should know more about the Amazons. Teach me now, are the Amazons butchers?&quot;<br>
<br>
The older woman's eyes flicked down to the starved man who was in no position to fight against the strength of the Queen holding him at death's doors.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cyreneraven>Cyrene Raven</A> at: 11/2/02 9:00:43 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=amazondelerium>Amazon DeLerium</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amazon Queen</span><br>  Posts: 404<br> <font color=#993300>(11/2/02 9:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=412.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Butchers?</span><hr size=1> That cold smile crept along her lips as she looked to Cyrene. A chuckle escaping her throat.<br>
&quot; You aren't the only one around here who have had sons. Many of us had. And no, the Amazons are not butchers...would you like me to tell you the story of a great war, a war between the Romans and the Amazons. A war started because the Romans would not accept that races of woman could not live without them. Would you like to hear how they tourtured and raped and killed our people, and sold many into slaves to be raped and abused by there masters. Those who would not submitt, were butchered. There body parts sent to the amazon nations as proof of what they would, could do? Hmmm?&quot;<br>
Her grip tightened on the males hair, nails digging into his scalp.<br>
&quot;These pigs slaughtered us by the hundreds. Themiscrya is the City of Amazons, the Greatest city , a sisterhood of strength and bonds. We have changed our ways slightly from the past. We too much change with the times. I remember a day, many many moons ago when I would of just walked in here, and killed him.....slowly. Not saying a word.<br>
<br>
As she spoke, the Amazon Guards around her circled them, not to close, but not to far. One, blocking the door, the only entrance or exit to the Tavern.<br>
<br>
&quot;The Labry's has seen its fair share of bloodshed throughout the time that we have been here. And no Roman is allowed within our lands. I see it as an act of war, defience. The wood he had to walk through to get to us was clearly marked as Amazon territory.  We, the Sisters of Themiscrya are Hera's Chosen. All of Greece and Rome know of us.&quot;<br>
<br>
She removed her sword and picked the male up by his hair, throwing him to the ground, she then moved in, posed for a strick, the tip of her blade shoved into his neck, enough for a trickle of blood to pour slowly out. Not bad enough to kill him. Her grey wolf, Lukoi came to stand besides her.<br>
<br>
&quot;He can have his freedom, He must declare here, and now, that woman are not mens toys to do what they please with, I want him to beg for his very life. Beg me to let him live his sorry exsistance of this Roman life. He does this, and he has till sunup to get as far from Amazon Terriroty as his feet can take him. If he is found in our territory at sunlight, he will be killed.&quot;<br>
<br>
Her seagreen eyes narrowed at the male at the end of her sword.<br>
<br>
&quot;It is, your choice.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cyreneraven>Cyrene Raven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tavern Owner and Merchant</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#993300>(11/2/02 11:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=412.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/cyreneamphipolis/cyrene005.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The Choice</span><hr size=1> Cyrene closed her eyes and bowed her head low to the Queen in respect.  Pale eyes turned to the stranger and the innkeeper sighed.<br>
<br>
He raised himself up on his knees and held his hands to his sides. &quot;Women, are not toys.  The idea turns my stomach to think such a thought.  I, too, have lost much to the Romans.&quot; With that the stranger turned his eyes upward, sorrow filled and void of life, he turned his head to one side exposing the wound in his neck.<br>
<br>
&quot;My son was trampled under the hooves of the horses that rode to my home with the intent to murder me.  In my home they found my wife, not me. They took my wife...took her light and then burned it.  I found her hanging with her body torn to pieces, my son's charred body on the road.&quot; The memories threatened to overtake him as the emotion cracked his voice and tore at his heart. The venom of his hatred for the hideous act that ended his family vomited from his throat to spill out onto those ears who would listen. &quot;ROME! That is who held the sword.  Her Legions preying on a small farm and a noble family. ROMAN LIFE?!&quot;<br>
<br>
Struggling for breath the stranger's hands trembled and he placed them on the floor. Meeting the Queen's eyes his voice seemed lost, rough yet clear. &quot;Do with me what you will, for I am not what you see.  The only thing I do know is, what worth would I have as a man, as a mortal, to beg for such a useless thing as a Roman life?  I have humbled myself before you, but I will not disrespect the memory of my wife and son by losing my honor in begging for my life. The one thing I have left in this life is revenge. I ask that if I die now unavenged, that you kill me quickly, so that I may start my work in another life.&quot;<br>
<br>
The older woman moved to right her chair and once it was settled back on four legs she took a heavy lean against it.  Holding her breath she stared between the Amazon Queen and the stranger.  She suddenly felt as Pandora did; the box open and the only option left was to watch, helpless, as chaos and distruction reigned. Death had been a constant at times in her life and she feared here she would witness it again. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=amazondelerium>Amazon DeLerium</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amazon Queen</span><br>  Posts: 405<br> <font color=#993300>(11/3/02 10:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=412.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/deleriuml9/images/del2.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Choice</span><hr size=1> She looked to Cyrene as the male spoke, then back to him. Rage still played like fire in her eyes. When he was done telling his tale, she looked back to Cyrene.<br>
<br>
&quot; So now that you hear his story, are the amazons the butchers or the Romans?&quot;<br>
<br>
Her eyes met the males and she withdrew her sword, sheathing it.<br>
<br>
&quot;Get up, and get out. I am sorry for the loss of your family, but it does not surprise me either what the Romans did to them.&quot;<br>
<br>
She turned her back and headed to the door.<br>
<br>
&quot;Be gone from the village by first light.&quot;<br>
<br>
With that, she stormed out of the tavern <p>         ~~* De'Lerium *~~ &lt;br&gt;<br>
